<concept id="concept-5409" xml:lang="en-us" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Introduction to organizing tests</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><author translate="no" type="creator" class="- topic/author ">Yen Nguyen &lt;yen.nguyen@katalon.com&gt;</author><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><keywords class="- topic/keywords "/></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p ">Organizing your tests is a crucial part of your daily testing activities. Since your project may have hundreds or thousands of tests, it is imperative that you organize them efficiently so you can find relevant tests quickly. </p><p class="- topic/p ">In <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-platform" class="- topic/ph "/>, you must first upload your test scripts using the Git repositories to <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-testops" class="- topic/ph "/>. See: <xref href="../upload-tests-via-git-repo/intro-git-test-project.dita" class="- topic/xref "/>. </p><p class="- topic/p "> Once uploading your test scripts from the Git repository, you can organize your tests in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-testops" class="- topic/ph "/> or <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/>. You can refer to the following documents:<ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="../Manage_Tests/Test_suite/manage-test-suite-in-TestOps/intro-manage-test-suite-in-TestOps.dita" class="- topic/xref "/></p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="../Manage_Tests/Test_suite/manage-test-cases-in-test-suite-ks/intro_manage_in_test_suites_in_Studio.dita" class="- topic/xref "/></p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><xref href="../Manage_Tests/Dynamic_Test_Suite/manage-dynamic-test-suite-ks/c_intro_dynamic-test-suite-ks.dita" class="- topic/xref "/></p></li></ul></p><p class="- topic/p ">If you want to run parallel tests with multiple browsers, you can add and manage your test suites in a test suite collection. See: <xref href="../Manage_Tests/Test-suite-collection/intro-manage-test-suites-in-test-suite-collection.dita" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p><p class="- topic/p "><ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-platform" class="- topic/ph "/> also supports third-party integration for organizing tests, such as:<ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Jira integration</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Xray integration</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">qTest integration</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">TestRail integration</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Azure DevOps Test Plans integration</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Rally integration</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">TestLink integration</p></li></ul></p></conbody></concept>